  vpc_security_group_ids = [aws_security_group.redshift_sg.id]
  subnet_group_name      = aws_redshift_subnet_group.redshift_subnet_group.name

  cluster_subnet_group_name = aws_redshift_subnet_group.redshift_subnet_group.name
  publicly_accessible       = false
  apply_immediately         = true

  skip_final_snapshot = true

  tags = {
    Name = "Redshift Cluster"
  }
}
```

**Notes:**
- Replace `your-redshift-bucket`, subnet IDs, VPC ID, and CIDR blocks with your actual values
- Update the master password and other sensitive values
- The IAM policy includes S3 access - modify permissions as needed for your use case
- Adjust `node_type` and `cluster_type` based on your requirements
- Multi-node clusters require `number_of_nodes` parameter

