output "codebuild_project_name" {
  value = aws_codebuild_project.cs_autograder.name
}

output "codebuild_project_arn" {
  value = aws_codebuild_project.cs_autograder.arn
}
```

**Important Notes:**
1. Replace `https://github.com/your-org/student-submissions.git` with your actual GitHub repository containing student code
2. Create a `buildspec.yml` file in your GitHub repo root with the test logic (sample shown in comments)
3. For production GitHub integration, use GitHub Apps webhooks or AWS CodeStar Connections
4. Add GitHub token as CodeBuild environment variable for private repos
5. Customize the buildspec for your specific CS class requirements (language, tests, etc.)

