```

**Note:** Create a `userdata.sh` file in the same directory with the following content for EC2 initialization:

```bash
#!/bin/bash
yum update -y
yum install -y httpd
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd
echo "<h1>Video Streaming Server - $(hostname)</h1><p>Load balanced across multiple instances!</p>" > /var/www/html/index.html
```

This configuration creates:
- VPC with public/private subnets and NAT gateway
- Application Load Balancer in public subnets
- Auto Scaling Group with 2-4 t3.medium instances in private subnets
- Route53 hosted zone and A record alias to ALB
- Proper security groups and health checks
- Launch template with user data for web server setup

